@*
    DECLARE-BANKRUPTCY CONFIRMATION MODAL — a guard against an accidental tap on the
    profile's "Declare bankruptcy" button. Lives in stable page DOM (included by the
    phone page and the host play page OUTSIDE their live-swapped regions), so a
    StateChanged re-render of the profile body can't destroy it mid-open and strand
    the backdrop — the same reason engine prompts were moved off Bootstrap modals.

    The trigger button (inside the swapped profile) opens this via Bootstrap's
    delegated data-bs-toggle and carries the target player's id; bankruptcy.js reads
    it off the show event's relatedTarget, stashes it on the confirm button, and
    invokes GamePlayHub.DeclareBankruptcy(playerId) on confirm.
*@
<div class="modal fade" id="bankruptcyConfirmModal" tabindex="-1"
     aria-labelledby="bankruptcyConfirmLabel" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered">
        <div class="modal-content border-danger">
            <div class="modal-header bg-danger text-white">
                <h5 class="modal-title" id="bankruptcyConfirmLabel">
                    <i class="bi bi-flag me-2"></i>Declare bankruptcy?
                </h5>
                <button type="button" class="btn-close btn-close-white" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                <p class="mb-0">
                    Are you sure you want to declare bankruptcy? This <strong>cannot be undone</strong> —
                    all your properties return to the bank and you are out of the game.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-outline-secondary" data-bs-dismiss="modal">Cancel</button>
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-danger" data-bankruptcy-confirm>
                    <i class="bi bi-flag me-1"></i> Declare bankruptcy
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>